Lake still settling after long winter.  Extremely high water.  Lake still very cold.

High water is causing lots of changes and lots of problems.

Partly cloudy- calm- not as clear due to more boats- however- still beautiful.
Perfect summer day. clarity less due to heavy rains + more boats.
Partly cloudy- choppy- storm moving in- lake affected by 7/30 storm.
Day much better than last week- reading improved- calm- perfect weather.
Bloom again at high level.  Lake at low level- May be cause. Clear calm day.

Perfect weather- ice out 3/25- level very low-need rain.

Rain-hard to find window to take reading- however much is needed.
Perfect day in ways- recent rains have helped stop drop in lake level.
Poor reading due to very heavy boat traffic.
Bad storm on 18th and heavy tree pollen makes for a bad reading.
Hard to get a window to take a reading between boats and bad weather.
Some improvement- boat traffic beginning to affect readings.
Perfect weather. Need rain badly. Lake level dropping every day.
First clear day in a week. Lower reading than average.
Nice early fall day. Readings reflect more bloom than normal.

First day all spring that a reading was possible. Ice out 4/18/02
Heavy pollen- however 1st day in awhile reading possible--heavy rain lately
Heavy "big" boat traffic- hard to get good reading
Reading about normal for time of year
Pays to take reading in middle of week. Better than long term average
Lake appears ready to turn over- reason for low reading
Nice fall day. Bloom beginning to show- heavy at times
First day without rain in a long time- perfect day for color
Perfect weather in all respects - still some pollen on surface
Looks like summer of '03 will be great.
Boat traffic picking up - still find weather.

first really nice day in some time- pollen still heavy.

At this point- snow would be welcome.

Lake level so low that to come back to what it once was is unthinkable.  Boat landings and piers out of water.  Weeds now growing where once was sand.  Smaller lakes have dried up.  This holds true for most of northern Wisconsin.
Small bits of green algae like material prevalent near shore.  No pollen to speak of.  Two loons present.
Clear day.  Spotted one mature loon- one eagle.
surface pollen present.  noted 1 eagle- 2 loons (nesting)- muskrat
High pollen content in and on top of water.

Sam and I had a beautiful day to monitor Bolger Lake. The day reached 75 degrees F and the wind was calm.  We launched the canoe at the public boat landing- paddled the entire shoreline looking for AIS- completed Secchi- temp- and DO- and I snorkeled a high risk area at the south east end. Bolger is a crystal clear lake with several sandy shorelines and lots of curious minnows. There are long stretches of littoral zones- which lack any aquatic vegetation.

column1: INVASIVE SPECIES FOUND:   I identified and collected several Chinese Mystery Snails. The samples were delivered to Sandy Wickman at the DNR office in Rhinelander for further confirmation.  -  Reported by Stephanie Boismenue

Lake very high. Water has never been this cloudy green/brown in the 30 years I have lived on lake.
